      'A candlestick chart shows what happened to a stock\'s price each day in a single glyph. The body shows where it opened and closed; a green/silver candle means it closed higher than it opened, a red candle means it closed lower. The thin wicks above and below show the highest and lowest prices reached during the day.',
      'Volume is the second half of the picture — the number of shares that changed hands. Big volume on a price move tells you institutional money is involved. Big price move with no volume usually means thin retail noise that won\'t hold.',
