      'When you read a 24-hour news feed, ask three questions: (1) Is this priced in already? (2) Does it affect this specific company or the whole sector? (3) What\'s the second-order effect? An oil price crash hurts oil refiners directly but helps airlines (lower fuel costs) and consumers (lower petrol). The second-order effects are where alpha lives.',
